title: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
chunks.html_content: As an employer covering the cost of your employees’ subscriptions and professional fees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
As an employer covering the cost of your employees’ subscriptions and professional fees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
chunks.html_content:
You don’t have to report anything to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) or pay tax and National Insurance if all of the following apply:

  • you pay the organisation yourself directly or if your employee pays the fee or subscription and you pay them back
  • the organisation is on ‘list 3’, HMRC’s list of approved professional bodies
  • you have exemptions (these have replaced dispensations) covering your fees and subscriptions

You do have to report the value of subscriptions and professional fees if you provide them as part of a salary sacrifice arrangement.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
Salary sacrifice arrangements
You don’t have to report anything to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) or pay tax and National Insurance if all of the following apply:

  you pay the organisation yourself directly or if your employee pays the fee or subscription and you pay them back
  the organisation is on ‘list 3’, HMRC’s list of approved professional bodies
  you have exemptions (these have replaced dispensations) covering your fees and subscriptions

You do have to report the value of subscriptions and professional fees if you provide them as part of a salary sacrifice arrangement.

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
If the organisation is included in ‘list 3’
chunks.html_content:
If any of the subscriptions or fees you cover aren’t exempt, you may have to report the costs to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) and deduct and pay tax and National Insurance on them.

You won’t need to pay or report anything if you cover subscriptions or fees for an organisation included in list 3 either:

  • by paying the organisation directly
  • if your employee pays and you pay them back
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
If the organisation is included in ‘list 3’
If any of the subscriptions or fees you cover aren’t exempt, you may have to report the costs to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) and deduct and pay tax and National Insurance on them.
You won’t need to pay or report anything if you cover subscriptions or fees for an organisation included in list 3 either:

  by paying the organisation directly
  if your employee pays and you pay them back

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
If the organisation isn’t included in ‘list 3’
chunks.html_content:
If you pay them directly, add the cost of the fee or subscription to your employee’s earnings when deducting Class 1 National Insurance (but not PAYE tax) through your payroll.

If your employee pays and you pay them back:

  • add the cost of the fee or subscription to your employee’s earnings
  • deduct and pay PAYE tax and Class 1 National Insurance through your payroll
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
If the organisation isn’t included in ‘list 3’
If you pay them directly, add the cost of the fee or subscription to your employee’s earnings when deducting Class 1 National Insurance (but not PAYE tax) through your payroll.
If your employee pays and you pay them back:

  add the cost of the fee or subscription to your employee’s earnings
  deduct and pay PAYE tax and Class 1 National Insurance through your payroll

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
chunks.html_content:
If the value of subscriptions and professional fees is less than the amount of salary given up, report the salary amount instead.

These rules don’t apply to arrangements made before 6 April 2017 - check when the rules will change.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: subscriptions and professional fees
Salary sacrifice arrangements
If the value of subscriptions and professional fees is less than the amount of salary given up, report the salary amount instead.
These rules don’t apply to arrangements made before 6 April 2017 - check when the rules will change.
